column1: There two gauges that overlap this gauge at the same location, one records an annaul average of 2.6 inces more for 1874 to 1883 and the other and average of 6 inches more for 1938 to 1940. There are various notes in the reocords about this gauge leaking
The Jan 1940 record has anote saying the reading was adjusted for snow, the reading has been kept in this record
